<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1602,1734]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1602,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pseudorostral lobes meeting for some distance at the front of carapace. Pereonite 
<number box="[1183,1197,1602,1626]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
visible in both sexes. Basis of third maxilliped not produced. Second pereopod with ischium. Female with well-developed exopods on pereopods 
<number box="[274,288,1674,1698]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[345,361,1674,1698]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
, and usually with a rudimentary exopod on pereopod 
<number box="[973,989,1674,1698]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
. Male with well-developed exopods on first four pereopods. Male with 
<number box="[507,521,1710,1734]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="5.0">5</number>
pairs of pleopods. Endopod of the uropod with 
<number box="[1057,1071,1710,1734]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
article.
</paragraph>
